<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="137">There is a special rule for vouchers that have only <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="137">Project</strong> or <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="137">Ledger</strong> lines, when a sales tax group or item sales tax group is selected on the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="137">Ledger</strong> line. This rule is controlled by Enable independent sales tax calculation feature for general journals. When this feature is turned off, the tax amount of the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="137">Ledger</strong> line uses the debit/credit direction of the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="137">Project</strong> line. When the feature is turned on, the tax amount of the <strong sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="137">Ledger</strong> line uses its own debit/credit direction. The following tables show the rule for each scenario.</p>
