<h2 id="determine-the-sales-tax-amount-and-account-on-the-voucher" sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="153">Determine the sales tax amount and account on the voucher</h2>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="155">When you post sales taxes, the main account is retrieved from the ledger posting group profile. When sales taxes are receivable, the system uses the Sales Tax Receivable account that is specified in the profile. For sales taxes that are payable, the system uses Sales Tax Payable account that is specified in the profile.</p>
<p sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="157">The following table shows the generic rule.</p>
<table sourcefile="articles/finance/general-ledger/sales-tax-calculation-on-general-journal.md" sourcestartlinenumber="159">
<thead>
